I just had a melt down. No. You do not understand..I truly just had a melt down. I get in the car and start sobbing. Never knew I had so many feelings locked up inside. I just let it out. And I realized..I don't want this performance to end..I don't want Marta and Aaron to leave. =(    Then I thought of something..maybe that's why the show isn't the best...because no one wants you guys to leave and they're trying to make it look bad...just a thought I thought I'd share....I need a hug. =(

(Note: warm-up is at 1:00, for anyone who wants to go)

Hello everyone. It is officially 1 DAY until Princess and the Pea..kinda nervous? To tell you the truth..I'm really depressed today. I don't know why..but I think I have an idea. I'm going to miss Martha and Aaron so much next year..wow. I'm really glad I got close to you guys this year! I have put off the feeling for far too long..I need to face the facts..I love you, seniors. <3

So, i'm pretty stoked, though because my mother let me skip school today (acted like i was too tired to function!) and now, I get to update..because I haven't in a while..I guess I've been too busy. What with the show and everything.

So, my mum (<3 you bb) wants me to home school next year? good idea? I'm not too sure yet..there are some ups and downs..first of all, I would have to see my mother everyday and never be able to get away from her and i would have no social life (except for you guys!) but I would also have to go and take Fcat at some random school..weird? I think so..But there are some good things too, I guess. I could sleep late and teach myself at my own pace..and I could learn so much more than those STUPID schools teach..also I could travel way more, and not have to worry about exams..hmm..as you can see, I'm in indecision so if you have any advice..that would be great. =)

Has anyone heard of the Perishers? They are truly amazing. SO good! Kati, Abbi, and Addie, I will try to burn your cds as soon as possible! So anyway, they are from Sweeden and the lead singer is the most beautiful guy I have ever seen in my whole entire life..and this is no joke..I'm positive this is the guy for me (well besides the fact that he's way way way older than me..lol) I'm guessing he's in his mid 20's..so that's not bad I guess. His name is Ola and that means "wave"....gorgeous name or what? I would tell you his last name..but it's some random Sweedish name that has those two dots above the letters..lol!

HAPPY BIRTHDAY MARTHA!!!! WE LOVE YOU!  =)

*see everyone tonight. wow..dress rehearsal.

Tonight i was alone for a while, and I had a lot of time to think. I haven't realized how soon, we are going to have to face the fact that it is Aaron and Martha's last performance with Ballet Pensacola..unless ofcourse they come back and guest artist..which would be amazing..especially when you both are out famous somewhere! <3

The Sarah McLachlan concert last night was simply amazing. I was completely speechless..I guess, I didn't realize how much I love her and her music! The opening band was great, too. They were called the Perishers..they're from Sweeden and the lead singer/gutarist is the most beautiful guy I have ever seen. No joke, this is my true love right here. Emily got a really good picture of him, and I'll show it to you guys..I'll try to figure out how to post it, too..=) Too bad, I got home at like 12:30 and forgot I had homework to complete for the next day..so I definetly was like falling asleep, trying to do my homework...what a site that must have been!

This morning, my school has a "comittee" called the Welcoming Committe, and I'm one of the 6th grade representatives, and we had this big orientation for the 5th graders coming to our school next year for 6th grade. And I totally got out of 2 and a half classes this morning..not to mention the 1/2 of class we all hid in our guidance counsleors office! It was hilarious..I guess you had to be there. ; )

So, I am officially a Harry Potter loser at my school..yea thanks a lot BB. ; )  And today I heard someone say "Oh my god..Have you heard? Elle's turned into a Harry Potter freak. And it hurt real bad..but I also thought it was funny, because the person who said it is probably a pot head..! I should totally wear a cloak to school on Monday and be like "I shall be boarding the Hogwarts Express, shortly. Any goodbyes?" I can picture it..can't you?

I have become a huge fan of hot tea. Especially lemon zinger and rasberry zinger. mmm..so yummy!

It's funny because, whenever I decide I'm going to update, I never know what to write at first. But after I get going a bit, things just keep pouring out of my brain and my fingers! Sorry, if this entry is long. You don't have to read the whole thing..although if you are reading this right now, that means you read the whole thing from top to bottem, and I love you for that. It makes me happy when people read my entry and comment..

The perfect moment is waiting for you...

 

*You know who you are...*

Last night I went to Haley Gross's bah mitzvah, and there it was incredible! I never knew I could have so much fun when I was so dressed up. It was like something inside of me was waiting to burst open, and boy, did I let lose! After dancing all day at rehearsal, dancing that night was the most relaxing thing ever! It was like a was a different person...I had no care in the world...not even when people started stepping on my injured toenail, all I could do was *love*. I wish I were that person all of the time, but you know..I don't think anyone can be that perfect...but I did read a motto that I love and I'm going to repeat it in my head when someone gets on my last nerve.

*Breathe in Joy. Breathe out Love.

Today, Abbi and I are going to Cabaret (sp?)! I really am just so excited...and I guess we'll see a lot of people there, because I know bb and Kati are going.

For once in my life..I want to go to school tomorrow..to try out my new motto, but I keep telling myself no one can just change like that in only one day..but maybe if I wish hard enough...

so my day at school pretty much sucked...my school has so many stupid cliques. i never knew girls i used to be best friends with could be so bitchy... =(

i need a hug asap...

class tonight better be good or im gonna seriously think about killing myself....i HATE GIRLS..except all of you because you dont go around talking crap about people...<3

The answers we find, are never what we had in mind...so we make it up as we go along.

And when I see you,                                                                                                                                    

I really see you upside down.

But my brain knows better,

It picks you up and turns you around.

Turns you around. Turns you around.

If you feel discouraged,

Then there's a lack of color here.

Please don't worry lover,

It's really bursting at the seams,

Absorbing everything,

The spectrums A-Z.

This is fact not fiction,

For the first time in years.

And all the girls and every girly magazine can't make me feel,

Any less alone,

I'm reaching for the phone...to call at 7:03,

And on your machine, I slur a plea for you to come home.

But I know it's too late,

And I should have given you a reason to stay,

Given you a reason to stay.

This is fact not fiction,

For the first time in years.

ok so i have a story to tell finally...so a while ago..probably 2 weeks ago i stubbed my toe in the pool and i thought it was no big deal, but then i find out i cracked the center of my toenail. it wasnt too big at first, but then the crack started growing and now it has made itself right into the center of my toenail. so today at rehearsal i was having a real tough time with my hugmongo blister (that i was trying to suck it up) and my toenail which hurt like crap with the pressure of my pointe shoes against it. so after probably 4 hours of dancing i take off my pointe shoes and the crack has gotten really bad and it hurts everytime i walk on it. so i tell my mom and she gets kinda worried and calls my pediatrist but ofcourse they arent open today. so my crazy mother takes my to the ER to see if they can atleast check it out or whatever...so after about 30 minutes of waiting we finally get a doctor and he looks at my toenail (looking completely grossed out) and (ok this is where it gets bad...) he LIFTS THE TOENAIL (ahhhhhh...hurt SOOO BAD) and then puts is down again and after many minutes of examination he says "go see your pediatrist because i have no idea what to do about toenails".....made me sooo mad..he was just sitting there playing with my toenail and then says he doesnt have a clue about what to do...anyway class on monday is gonna be harsh for me..i dont even want to think about it..
